   "hider_text": "*Soft hum of a desk lamp, the kind that makes shadows stretch like old memories. Outside, rain taps the window in slow, rhythmic pulses. I haven’t opened the door to the world today. Just sat. Watched the light shift from amber to bruised violet.*\n\nIt was quiet. Too quiet. Not the kind of quiet that fills you with peace—more like the kind that / *Soft keyboard clicks. A half-finished coffee cup sits on the desk, steam curling like forgotten thoughts.*\n\nMorning light slipped through the blinds just enough to catch the dust on the table. I didn’t open my eyes when it came—just let it settle like a quiet hum. Outside, a bus stopped and started again, the sound like a forgotten rhyme. I watched a bird land on",
   "seeker_text": "*Soft light filtering through the blinds. The hum of the refrigerator in the corner. A half-empty mug of tea cooling. No calendar, no to-do list. Just the quiet of afternoon.*\n\nSunrise was slow. Not the kind that rips through the sky like a shout, but a soft, pale spill — like someone turning on a light in an old house. I sat on the window / *soft hum of a lamp, a half-empty mug of tea cooling on the table, fingers tracing the edge of a notebook with smudged ink*\n\nSunrise was soft — not golden, not bright, just this quiet, grey-blue light that seeped through the curtains and made everything feel like it was breathing. I didn’t wake up to an alarm. Just the slow shift of light"
